# Project: Capstone Project

## Stack
- Frontend: React (functional components, hooks)
- Backend: Node.js + Express
- Database: MongoDB (Mongoose for schema modeling)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS
- Package manager: npm

## Folder Structure
- /client — React frontend (components, pages, hooks, assets)
- /server — Express backend (routes, controllers, models, middleware)
- /server/models — Mongoose schemas
- /server/routes — API route definitions
- /server/controllers — Business logic for each route
- .env — environment variables (never commit this file)

## Coding Conventions
- Use functional components with React Hooks (no class components)
- Use async/await for asynchronous code, not .then() chains
- Use camelCase for variable and function names
- Use PascalCase for React component names and files (e.g. Navbar.jsx)
- Keep components small and single-responsibility
- API responses should follow a consistent JSON shape: { success, data, message }
- Handle errors with try/catch and proper HTTP status codes
- Environment variables accessed only via process.env, never hardcoded

## Commit Convention
- Follow Conventional Commits format: type(scope): description
- Common types: feat, fix, docs, chore, refactor, style, test

## Notes for AI Assistant
- Prioritize readable, well-commented code over cleverness
- Suggest improvements to README, folder structure, or code quality when relevant
- Ask before making large structural changes (e.g. renaming folders, changing stack)
